A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 5, 2025, as Latino Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Georgia is home to more than one million people of Latin American heritage
3 who are part of the economic, social, and cultural fabric of the state, and their daily
4 contributions need to be recognized, uplifted, and honored as integral to Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, Latinos in Georgia are a young community yet are very active in all sectors.
6 Latino men participate in the workforce in Georgia at higher rates than any other
7 demographic group, Latinas turn out to vote at higher rates than the national average, and a
8 third of the community is under 18 years old and actively working to pursue their educational
9 aspirations; and
10 WHEREAS, Latinos have been an integral part of building the state and its economic
11 standing, including workers in carpet manufacturing in Whitfield County, the poultry
12 industry in Hall County, the agricultural sector in rural areas and South Georgia, in retail
13 through entrepreneurship as a self-sufficiency strategy, in the military and law enforcement,
14 professionally in corporations and businesses, in the public and nonprofit sector, and
15 academically through institutions of higher education; and
