16 WHEREAS, Latinos are well known for their appreciation of family and community as well
17 as their joy and optimism; and
18 WHEREAS, Latinos provide an immense amount of arts and culture to the State of Georgia
19 and have a vast array of artisans and folkloric groups from all nations in Latin America and
20 the Caribbean, from Mexico to Argentina as well as from Puerto Rico and Brazil to Peru; and
21 WHEREAS, this diverse community will continue growing to represent a significant
22 percentage of Georgia, and it is expected its representation and civic participation will only
23 increase.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body recognize February 5, 2025, as Latino Day at the state capitol.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
27 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
28 public and the press.
